{"id": "EUVD-2022-1450", "enisaUuid": "6eeb71d0-e331-3898-bc04-711d63ec4569", "description": "`@chainsafe/libp2p-noise` contains TypeScript implementation of noise protocol, an encryption protocol used in libp2p. `@chainsafe/libp2p-noise` before 4.1.2 and 5.0.3 does not correctly validate signatures during the handshake process. This may allow a man-in-the-middle to pose as other peers and get those peers banned. Users should upgrade to version 4.1.2 or 5.0.3 to receive a patch. There are currently no known workarounds.", "datePublished": "2022-03-17T16:40:11", "dateUpdated": "2025-04-23T18:46:39", "baseScore": 8.1, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://github.com/ChainSafe/js-libp2p-noise/security/advisories/GHSA-j3ff-xp6c-6gcc", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-24759", "https://github.com/ChainSafe/js-libp2p-noise/pull/130", "https://github.com/ChainSafe", "https://github.com/ChainSafe/js-libp2p-noise/releases/tag/v5.0.3"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-24759", "GHSA-j3ff-xp6c-6gcc"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.12, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "540b0924-83a8-3ebc-9a59-d6ca196cba78", "product": {"name": "js-libp2p-noise"}, "product_version": "< 4.1.2"}, {"id": "e69f8d05-d669-3303-95a1-6f7533e23a31", "product": {"name": "js-libp2p-noise"}, "product_version": "5.0.0, < 5.0.3"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "724f2b48-3f29-36ec-881d-d60e7051bd0b", "vendor": {"name": "ChainSafe"}}], "isExploited": false}